                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "0be92c40-ded4-48ee-a466-07236da03b9f"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "f8fde2dc66fa4b8f845de",
            "questionText": "A delivery company's electric van accelerates from rest to a speed of $!$20 \\text{ m/s}$!$ on a horizontal road. During this acceleration, the motor does $!$500,000 \\text{ J}$!$ of work. After this, the van travels up a hill, gaining $!$10\\text{ m}$!$ in vertical height. If the van's mass is $!$1500\\text{ kg}$!$, what is the total change in the van's mechanical energy from the start of the acceleration to reaching the height of $!$10\\text{ m}$!$ on the hill?",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "794bf84a5c7f403cb4c28",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by finding the energy the van gains while accelerating. To do so, we need to calculate its kinetic energy once it reaches $!$20\\text{ m/s}$!$. Please identify which formula correctly represents the kinetic energy of an object.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "0f719348-94a2-4b8e-8cd8-638039f27e60"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$E_k = m v$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$E_k = \\frac{1}{2} m v^2$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$E_k = mgh$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "5979250eb478434caec39",
                    "stepText": "Great. Now, using the formula you've chosen, calculate the kinetic energy of the van after accelerating from rest to $!$20\\text{ m/s}$!$ with a mass of $!$1500 \\text{ kg}$!$. Provide the numerical result.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "300000"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "J",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "0f719348-94a2-4b8e-8cd8-638039f27e60"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "2d644e6e10424615b7886",
                    "stepText": "Next, as the van climbs a hill and gains vertical height, it also gains gravitational potential energy. Identify the correct formula to calculate gravitational potential energy.",
